In [588]:
#Correcting negative Experience

negativeExperience=df[df['Experience'] < 0]
positiveExperience=df[df['Experience'] > 0]

#need to watch this negativeExperience
print ("Total number of ppl with negative experience:",negativeExperience['Experience'].count())
print("People having negative experinece:\n",negativeExperience['Experience'].value_counts())

#Replace negative experience value with median value of the positive experience of the same educationa nd age. 

for id in negativeExperience['ID']:
    age = df.loc[np.where(df['ID']==id)]["Age"].tolist()[0]
    education= df.loc[np.where(df['ID']==id)]["Education"].tolist()[0]
    df_possitiveExperience = positiveExperience[(positiveExperience['Age'] == age) & (positiveExperience['Education'] == education)]
    if df_possitiveExperience.empty :
        df_negative_Experience = negativeExperience[(negativeExperience['Age'] == age) & (negativeExperience['Education'] == education)]
        exp = round(df_negative_Experience['Experience'].median())
    else:
        exp = round(df_possitiveExperience['Experience'].median())
    df.loc[df.loc[np.where(df['ID']==id)].index, 'Experience'] = abs(exp)

In [608]:
## function to get confusion matrix in a proper format
def draw_cm( actual, predicted ):
    cm = confusion_matrix( actual, predicted)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True,  fmt='.2f', xticklabels = [0,1] , yticklabels = [0,1] )
    plt.ylabel('Observed')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.show()

from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve

logit_roc_auc = roc_auc_score(Y_Expr_test, logreg.predict(X_Expr_test))
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(Y_Expr_test, logreg.predict_proba(X_Expr_test)[:,1])
plt.figure()
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label='Logistic Regression (area = %0.2f)' % logit_roc_auc)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1],'r--')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('Receiver operating characteristic')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.savefig('Log_ROC')
plt.show()

Business Insight¶

Confusion Matrix:¶

True Positive (observed=1,predicted=1):

Predicted that custometer will purchase a personal loan and the customer was liable for loan

False Positive (observed=0,predicted=1):

Predicted that custometer will purchase a personal loan and the customer was not liable for loan

True Negative (observed=0,predicted=0):

Predicted that custometer will not purchase a personal loan and the customer was not liable for loan

False Negative (observed=1,predicted=0):

Predicted that custometer will not purchase a personal loan and the customer was liable for loan

Important features¶

Mortgage has coefficients value as 0 so these feature doesn't help model in predicting target variable. Education_undergrad,CD Account,Family_two,Family_one are the top features based on the coefficient

Observations for Model With Experience and Metrics¶

From the two models its evident that the accuracy and Precision are better for the model with "Experience"

Significantly less false positive

Better knowledge about which group likely to accept and reject loan offer.

Better campaigning approach required for family with "one" and "two" family member and pursue them to accept the loan

Better campaigning approach required for undergrad customers and pursue them to accept the loan
